u"Make sure you can run daff from the command-line as just \"daff\" - if not,\nreplace \"daff\" in the driver and command lines above with the correct way\nto call it. Add --no-color if your terminal does not support ANSI colors."
u"daff can produce and apply tabular diffs.\n"
u"  daff merge [--inplace] parent.csv a.csv b.csv\n"
u"The --inplace option to patch and merge will result in modification of a.csv.\n"
u"If you need more control, here is the full list of flags:\n"
u"  daff diff [--output OUTPUT.csv] [--context NUM] [--all] [--act ACT] a.csv b.csv\n"
u"     --act ACT:     show only a certain kind of change (update, insert, delete, column)\n"
u"     --all:         do not prune unchanged rows or columns\n"
u"     --all-rows:    do not prune unchanged rows\n"
u"     --all-columns: do not prune unchanged columns\n"
u"     --color:       highlight changes with terminal colors (default in terminals)\n"
u"     --context NUM: show NUM rows of context (0=none)\n"
u"     --context-columns NUM: show NUM columns of context (0=none)\n"
u"     --fail-if-diff: return status is 0 if equal, 1 if different, 2 if problem\n"
u"     --id:          specify column to use as primary key (repeat for multi-column key)\n"
u"     --ignore:      specify column to ignore completely (can repeat)\n"
u"     --index:       include row/columns numbers from original tables\n"
u"     --input-format [csv|tsv|ssv|psv|json|sqlite]: set format to expect for input\n"
u"     --eol [crlf|lf|cr|auto]: separator between rows of csv output.\n"
u"     --no-color:    make sure terminal colors are not used\n"
u"     --ordered:     assume row order is meaningful (default for CSV)\n"
u"     --padding [dense|sparse|smart]: set padding method for aligning columns\n"
u"     --table NAME:  compare the named table, used with SQL sources. If name changes, use 'n1:n2'\n"
u"     --unordered:   assume row order is meaningless (default for json formats)\n"
u"     -w / --ignore-whitespace: ignore changes in leading/trailing whitespace\n"
u"     -d EPS / --ignore-epsilon EPS: ignore small floating point differences\n"
u"  daff render [--output OUTPUT.html] [--css CSS.css] [--fragment] [--plain] diff.csv\n"
u"     --css CSS.css: generate a suitable css file to go with the html\n"
u"     --fragment:    generate just a html fragment rather than a page\n"
u"     --plain:       do not use fancy utf8 characters to make arrows prettier\n"
u"     --unquote:     do not quote html characters in html diffs\n"
u"     --www:         send output to a browser\n"
